Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{4}, separating whites from greens. Dice @tomato{2}(diced).

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large heavy-bottomed pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @ground turkey{20%ounce}, @Southwest spice blend{2%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until turkey is lightly browned and mostly cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step).

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Add garlic, scallion whites, and @tomato paste{2%unit}; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add diced tomatoes, @chicken stock concentrate{4%unit}, @cream cheese{4%tablespoon}, and @sugar{1.5%teaspoon} to pot with turkey mixture; stir until well combined.

> Use 3 tsp sugar for 8 servings.

Stir in @kidney beans{1%unit} and their liquid and @water{3%cups}; bring to a simmer and cook until tomatoes are softened and turkey is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat.

> Use 6 cups water for 8 servings.

Stir in half the @Mexican cheese blend{1%cup} and as much @hot sauce{2%teaspoon} as you like; taste and season with salt and pepper.

Divide soup between #bowls{}; top with scallion greens and remaining Mexican cheese blend. Serve.